{"word":"μηδέ","slug":"μηδέ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>μηδέ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:μή\">μή</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δέ\">δέ</a></el>] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ neg.\">neg.</a> particle used in escalation of negation<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> in continuation of a negation, <b>and not, nor <a href='B:470 6:25'>Mt 6:25</a>; <a href='B:470 22:29'>22:29</a>; <a href='B:480 12:24'>Mk 12:24</a>; <a href='B:490 14:12'>Lk 14:12</a>; <a href='B:530 5:8'>1 Cor 5:8</a>; <a href='B:690 2:15'>1 J 2:15</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> in negation that connotes a climax of possibilities <b>don’t even <a href='B:480 2:2'>Mk 2:2</a>; <a href='B:480 3:20'>3:20</a>; <a href='B:480 8:26'>8:26</a>; <a href='B:530 5:11'>1 Cor 5:11</a>; <a href='B:560 5:3'>Eph 5:3</a>; <a href='B:600 3:10'>2 Th 3:10</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:μηδαμῶς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:μηδείς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}